  #dsa concept and pattern

  concept : greedy + sprting
    pattern : array transformation to satisfy unique. 


  int minIncrementForUnique(vector<int>& nums) {
    sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
    long long moves = 0;
    int prev = -1;

    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
        if (nums[i] <= prev) {
            // Need to increment current number to be greater than prev
            moves += (prev + 1 - nums[i]);
            nums[i] = prev + 1;
        }
        prev = nums[i];
    }

    return (int)moves;
}

🔍 Explanation
  Sort the array → duplicates will be adjacent.
Track prev → the last unique number we’ve fixed.
For each number:
If nums[i] <= prev, we must increment it to prev+1.
Add the difference to moves.
Update nums[i].
Return total moves.


